        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1351003669,
        "creation_date": 1351003669,
        "body": "<p>Why dont you just change approach?<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://kb.mozillazine.org/Creating_a_new_Firefox_profile_on_Windows\" rel=\"nofollow\">Create firefox profile<\/a> which will be clean and name it somehow you know what it is. e.g. <code>SELENIUM<\/code><\/li>\n<li><p>When initializing the Webdriver: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> ProfilesIni allProfiles = new ProfilesIni();\n FirefoxProfile desiredProfile = allProfiles.getProfile(\"SELENIUM\");\n WebDriver driver = new FirefoxDriver(desiredProfile);\n<\/code><\/pre><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>That way, you assure that this profile will be used anytime you do the tests...<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 13033155,
        "question_id": 13033071
    }],
